A wonderful site, I hope it will address ALL the issues, and help those still in need of healing. The side I represent is different than most, but still Nam is thing that changed me forever without ever being there. Waking up in the 60's with a death warrant in your wallet (draft card) made taking drugs a &quot;so what&quot; attitude, why not risk brain cells when Nam will get you anyway. The counter culture grew into the SDS and resistance side of the 60's directly due to Nam, drugs, and the reality that America was out to kill you. Stir in sex, the pill, freedom, and the absolute necessity to question authority or be drafted, and the movement grew. Yes, those of us saw draftee's and enlisted men as baby killers and fools, but we also saw them as victims, passive and powerless victims. I salute the resisters, the protesters for putting it on the line, not the draftee's who let it happen to them. America should acknowledge it true patriots, its loyal opposition.<br>
Perhaps this will be the forum for that recognizition to begin. <br><br>
-- shrink4u@irvine.quik.com (Dr.Barry Spatz) <br><br>
